title: What channel is Kansas City Royals-Houston Astros on? TV info for ALDS Game 3
text:
The American League Divisional Series between Kansas City and Houston is all tied at one game apiece as the action moves to Minute Maid Park on Sunday for Game 3..
Astros ace Dallas Keuchel, who paced the AL with 20 victories this season, will take the mound against the Royals' Edinson Volquez.
The contest begins at 4 p.m. and will be televised by the MLB Network.
Here's how to catch the MLB Network in Central New York:
Time Warner: Channel 306 (SD & HD) Verizon Fios: Channel 586 (HD) and 86 (SD) DirectTV: Channel 213 (SD & HD) Dish Network: Channel 152 (SD & HD) New Visions: Channel 767 (HD) and 75 (SD)
